{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1603273162,"nonce":"dZcHBEbRptw10gRjJHQlHFmSV5U=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo0NDQ3ODcwNDM="},"target":"e987978d0671ab109c67376515a19a4475848d76aa45c32f8bea38b7c01f48e9","message":"-----------\nI was wondering if it would be possible to include this new annotation tool from KEGG into Galaxy.\n\nhttps://www.genome.jp/tools/kofamkoala/ \n\nThere is a small program KofamScan (uses HMMER \u0026 Ruby) to simplify the job. The K-number hmms are downloaded as a database and one uses simple text files to select which subsets of K-numbers to search against.\n\nI think this would complement the InterProScan annotations very well as only ECs are given by InterProScan and not K-numbers; the latter being more specific.\n\n----------------------","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1603273195,"nonce":"BFos1OaYFGgyRBrcfPzRCyDFKkc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo0NDQ3ODczMDU="},"target":"e987978d0671ab109c67376515a19a4475848d76aa45c32f8bea38b7c01f48e9","message":"-----------\nI was wondering if it would be possible to include this new annotation tool from KEGG into Galaxy.\n\nhttps://www.genome.jp/tools/kofamkoala/ \n\nThere is a small program KofamScan (uses HMMER \u0026 Ruby) to simplify the job. The K-number hmms are downloaded as a database and one uses simple text files to select which subsets of K-numbers to search against.\n\nI think this would complement the InterProScan annotations very well as only ECs are given by InterProScan and not K-numbers; the latter being more specific.\n\n----------------------\n\nConda package here: https://anaconda.org/bioconda/kofamscan","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1603273151,"nonce":"wwhwhpzCRywtfJJsvrOxMq2xS98=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDM5MDI4OTExOTE="},"added":["new software"],"removed":[]}]}